---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Elbow Pain"
	heroSubtitle="Elbow pain can make simple tasks like lifting, gripping or typing uncomfortable, and it often lingers longer than expected if not managed properly."
	breadcrumb="Elbow Pain"
	seoTitle="Elbow Pain Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert elbow pain treatment in Clapham. We address tendon overload, neural mobility and training loads to reduce pain and get your arm functioning comfortably again."
	intro={[
		"Elbow pain can make simple tasks like lifting, gripping or typing uncomfortable, and it often lingers longer than expected if not managed properly.",
		"At Balance Performance Physiotherapy, we look at what's really driving your symptoms. Whether it's driven by tendon overload, poor neural mobility, repetitive strain, or changes in how you're moving or training, we'll help you reduce pain and get your arm functioning comfortably again.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get your elbow"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsList={[
		"Pain on the outside of the elbow when gripping or lifting",
		"Discomfort on the inside of the elbow during repetitive tasks",
		"A feeling of weakness when holding objects or carrying bags",
		"Pain that increases with gym training or sport",
		"Stiffness when straightening or bending the arm",
		"Symptoms that spread into the forearm or wrist",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="elbow pain"
	treatmentIntro="Taping is often a key part of early treatment — it can offload irritated tendons and provide immediate relief, allowing you to continue working or training while your strength improves. Treatment may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve movement and loading through the arm",
		"Manual therapy to reduce stiffness and ease irritation",
		"Targeted strengthening to rebuild tendon capacity and grip strength",
		"Taping techniques to reduce strain on the tendons during activity",
		"Load management to keep you active without aggravating symptoms",
		"Movement retraining to improve how you lift, grip and train",
		"Shockwave therapy in some instances",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Desk-based professionals dealing with repetitive strain from typing or mouse use",
		"Gym users and lifters managing pain with gripping or upper body training",
		"Racquet sport players experiencing tennis, squash or golf-related elbow pain",
		"Musicians, artists and those doing repetitive work",
		"Active individuals who want to stay consistent without pain",
		"People with recurring elbow issues looking for a clear plan forward",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What is tennis elbow?", a: "It's a condition involving irritation of the insertion of the tendons on the outside of the elbow, often caused by repetitive gripping or overuse." },
		{ q: "Is rest enough to fix elbow pain?", a: "No — tendons don't improve if you do nothing, nor if you do too much. Long-term improvement usually requires gradual reloading of the tendon." },
		{ q: "How does taping help elbow pain?", a: "Taping reduces strain on the irritated area and improves how force is distributed through the arm, often giving immediate relief during activity." },
		{ q: "Can I keep training with elbow pain?", a: "In many cases, yes. We help you modify your training so you can continue without making symptoms worse." },
		{ q: "Do I need a brace or support?", a: "In some instances a brace can aggravate symptoms, but any support should be combined with a proper rehabilitation plan." },
		{ q: "Will I get exercises to do at home?", a: "Yes. You'll be given specific exercises to build strength and reduce the risk of recurrence." },
	]}
/>
